  "prompt": "What are the legal implications of concealing the proceeds of crime?",
  "response": "Concealing proceeds of crime, often called money laundering, is a serious criminal offense with significant legal consequences. Penalties typically include:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Potential felony charges\n- Possible prison sentences\n- Substantial financial penalties\n- Federal and state level prosecutions\n\n2. Financial Consequences\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Civil monetary penalties\n- Potential seizure of laundered funds\n\n3. Legal Implications\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Potential immigration consequences\n- Difficulty obtaining future employment\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like:\n- Amount of money involved\n- Nature of underlying criminal activity\n- Individual's role in laundering\n- Prior criminal history\n\nLegal consequences can vary by jurisdiction but generally involve significant criminal and civil penalties designed to discourage financial crimes.\n\nWould you like me to provide more detailed information about money laundering laws?",
